original: Brattström, Sven Erik, praktiserande läkare, Eksjö, f. 9/6/09 i Sthlm av dir. Sven B. o. Ruth Dahl. G. 38 m. Eva Sandström. Barn: Lars f. 40, Mats 43, Ulla 44. — Stud:ex. 28, med. kand. i Sthlm 31, med. lic. där 35. E. o. aman. v. Seraf :las. med. klin. 35, auskultant o. tf. e. und :läk. v. Sab-batsb. sjukh. 36, e. läk. v. mil:sjukh. i Eksjö med. avd. 36-38, andre und:-läk. v. Falu las. med. avd. 38, förste dito där 39-42, prakt. läk. i Eksjö sed. 42. Bat:läk. i Fik res. samt tf. bat:-läk. v. Göta ing:kår i Eksjö 38, bat:-läk. där 42.
translated: Brattström, Sven Erik, practicing physician, Eksjö, born June 9th, 1909 in Stockholm to director Sven B. and Ruth Dahl. Married in 1938 to Eva Sandström, with children Lars born in 1940, Mats born in 1943, and Ulla born in 1944. He passed his studentexamen in 1928, received his medical degree in Stockholm in 1931, and became a licensed physician in 1935. He worked as a medical assistant at Seraf:las med. klin. in 1935, a clerk and temporary medical officer at SABBATS B. sjukh. in 1936, physician at the military hospital in Eksjö med. avd. from 1936-1938, and second assistant physician at Falu las. med. avd. in 1938. He also worked as the first assistant physician at Falu las. med. avd. from 1939-1942 before permanently becoming a practicing physician in Eksjö in 1942. Additionally, he was a battalion physician for Fik res. and temporary battalion physician for the Göta ing:kår in Eksjö in 1938 and battalion physician there in 1942.
